Nov 16 2008 	london weekend	We booked our stay on the hotel website and received a substantial discount for booking online (we paid £75 for a double room and £75 for a twin room). This made the stay extremely good value for a hotel in a fantastic location in the lovely borough of Fulham just a couple of minutes walk from fulham broadway tube station and with a bus stop almost outside the hotel. Whats more, the hotel is one of very few in london that has a car park and allows guests to park for free (subject to space). This was a great bonus.The hotel itself looked nice from the outside and the reception, bar a and restaurant area all looked well kept. The rooms looked a little tired and could do with being updated but were a good size and were equipped with everything you could need. I read other reviews about terrible tv reception, but all i can say is that the terrestrial tv we viewed was fine in our room. The bathroom was again slightly dated but clean and functional.We ate the standard breakfast included in the room price and were pleasantly surprised at the broad selection of cereals, breads, pastries and fruit on offer which made a good start to the day.Overall, the hotel is dated and may not have been worth paying the full price but if you can book online it becomes very reasonably priced for its prime location and the parking facility.	
