Oct 15 2008 	A trip back to the 80's...	Firstly the good news: the location is good (assuming Chelsea don't have a home match, since the hotel backs onto Stamford Bridge stadium), having free off-road parking is great, and the staff are friendly and helpful. HOWEVER this hotel is best suited to the visually disabled with short hair and indiscriminate taste buds. In 3 different rooms it was impossible to get a good picture on any TV channels (no satellite despite what the phone holding message says), and worse, hot water was virtually unknown. Several times we stood shivering under the shower while the water supply disappeared for 5 - 10 mins. This is a basic for a hotel, and it's shocking that La Reserve can't supply it. Also the fruit juice in the breakfast buffet is noticeably watered-down... the sign of a cheapskate establishment. This hotel was clearly refurbished around 1984, and all the fittings are comically archetypical 80's (black moulded WC and washbasin anyone??). Since not one penny has been spent on the place since, many are also seriously worn and shoddy. One of the power sockets in the room was faulty and positively dangerous. Go to a Travelodge instead - soulless, but at least you're guaranteed the basics.	
